fields.name: Medal of Honor
fields.description: Highest military decoration awarded for valor in combat

fields.name: Distinguished Service Cross
fields.description: Second highest military decoration for extraordinary heroism

fields.name: Silver Star
fields.description: Third-highest military combat decoration for gallantry in action

fields.name: Legion of Merit
fields.description: Military award for exceptionally meritorious conduct

fields.name: Bronze Star
fields.description: Awarded for heroic or meritorious achievement in a combat zone

fields.name: Purple Heart
fields.description: Awarded to those wounded or killed while serving

fields.name: Air Force Cross
fields.description: Awarded for extraordinary heroism in combat operations

fields.name: Navy Cross
fields.description: Second highest decoration for valor in the U.S. Navy and Marine Corps

fields.name: Coast Guard Cross
fields.description: Second highest decoration for heroism in the U.S. Coast Guard

fields.name: Distinguished Flying Cross
fields.description: Awarded for heroism or extraordinary achievement in aerial flight

fields.name: Army Distinguished Service Medal
fields.description: Awarded for exceptionally meritorious service in a duty of great responsibility

fields.name: Navy Distinguished Service Medal
fields.description: Awarded for distinguished service in a significant position of responsibility

fields.name: Air Force Distinguished Service Medal
fields.description: Given for exceptional meritorious service in a duty of great responsibility

fields.name: Coast Guard Distinguished Service Medal
fields.description: Awarded for exceptionally meritorious service to the government

fields.name: Defense Superior Service Medal
fields.description: Recognizes superior meritorious service in a position of significant responsibility

fields.name: Defense Meritorious Service Medal
fields.description: Awarded for non-combat meritorious achievement or service

fields.name: Meritorious Service Medal
fields.description: Recognizes outstanding meritorious achievement or service

fields.name: Air Medal
fields.description: Awarded for heroic actions or meritorious service in aerial flight

fields.name: Combat Action Ribbon
fields.description: Awarded for active participation in ground or surface combat

fields.biography: General James Miller has served with distinction for over 35 years. He has commanded forces in multiple theaters and led several key NATO operations. His strategic vision has been instrumental in shaping modern military doctrine.

Lieutenant General Elizabeth Parker has been a trailblazer throughout her career. She was one of the first women to command a combat brigade and has served in various leadership positions across NATO. Her expertise in logistics has transformed how NATO conducts operations.

Colonel Jean Dupont is a decorated officer with extensive experience in special operations. He has led numerous high-risk missions and contributed significantly to counter-terrorism strategies within NATO. His tactical innovations have been adopted by multiple member nations.

General James Miller has served with distinction for over 35 years. He has commanded forces in multiple theaters and led several key NATO operations. His strategic vision has been instrumental in shaping modern military doctrine.
